\p
\v 33 He maketh my feet like hinds’ \add feet,\add* and setteth me upon my high places.
\p
\v 34 He teacheth my hands to war, so that a bow of steel is broken by mine arms.
\p
\v 35 Thou hast also given me the shield of thy salvation: and thy right hand hath holden me up, and thy gentleness hath made me great.
\p
\v 36 Thou didst enlarge my steps under me, that my feet did not slip.
\p
\v 37 I pursued mine enemies and did overtake them: neither did I turn again till they were consumed.
\p
\v 38 I wounded them that they were not able to rise: they fell under my feet.
\p
\v 39 For thou hast girded me with strength unto the battle: thou didst subdue under me those that rose up against me.
\p
\v 40 Thou hast also given me the necks of mine enemies; that I might destroy them that hate me.
\p
\v 41 They cried, but \add there was\add* none to save \add them: even\add* unto the LORD, but he answered them not.
\p
\v 42 Then did I beat them small as the dust before the wind: I did cast them out as the dirt in the streets.
\p
\v 43 Thou didst deliver me from the strivings of the peoples; \add and\add* thou didst make me the head of the nations: a people \add whom\add* I have not known shall serve me.
\p
\v 44 As soon as they hear of me, they shall obey me: the strangers shall submit themselves unto me.
\p
\v 45 The strangers shall fade away, and be afraid out of their close places.
\p
\v 46 The LORD liveth; and blessed \add be\add* my rock; and let the God of my salvation be exalted.
\p
\v 47 The God that avengeth me, and hath subdued the peoples under me.
\p
\v 48 He delivereth me from mine enemies: yea, thou liftest me up above those that rise up against me: thou hast delivered me from the violent man.
\p
\v 49 Therefore will I give thanks unto thee, O LORD, among the nations, and sing praises unto thy name.
\p
\v 50 Great deliverance giveth he to his king; and showeth mercy to his anointed, to David, and to his seed for evermore.
\c 19
\cl PSALM 19
\d To the chief Musician, A Psalm of David.
\p
\v 1 ¶ The heavens declare the glory of God; and the firmament showeth his handywork.
\p
\v 2 Day unto day uttereth speech, and night unto night showeth knowledge.
\p
\v 3 \add There is\add* no speech nor language, \add where\add* their voice is not heard.
\p
