\p
\v 5 Which \add is\add* as a bridegroom coming out of his chamber, \add and\add* rejoiceth as a strong man to run a race.
\p
\v 6 His going forth \add is\add* from the end of the heaven, and his circuit unto the ends of it: and there is nothing hid from the heat thereof.
\p
\v 7 The law of the LORD \add is\add* perfect, converting the soul: the testimony of the LORD \add is\add* sure, making wise the simple.
\p
\v 8 The statutes of the LORD \add are\add* right, rejoicing the heart: the commandment of the LORD \add is\add* pure, enlightening the eyes.
\p
\v 9 The fear of the LORD \add is\add* clean, enduring for ever: the judgments of the LORD \add are\add* true \add and\add* righteous altogether.
\p
