\p
\v 12 Who can understand \add his\add* errors? cleanse thou me from secret \add faults.\add*
\p
\v 13 Keep back thy servant also from presumptuous \add sins;\add* let them not have dominion over me: then shall I be upright, and I shall be innocent from the great transgression.
\p
\v 14 Let the words of my mouth, and the meditation of my heart, be acceptable in thy sight, O LORD, my strength, and my redeemer.
\c 20
\cl PSALM 20
\d To the chief Musician, A Psalm of David.
\p
\v 1 ¶ The LORD hear thee in the day of trouble; the name of the God of Jacob defend thee;
\p
\v 2 Send thee help from the sanctuary, and strengthen thee out of Zion;
\p
